cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CY

The paper focuses on the practices and experiences of people looking for software, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves understanding the criteria people use when searching for software, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of community sites such as Stack Overflow and GitHub is also mentioned, which could fall under the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
